[Crimean-Congo hemorrhagic fever has been reported in Iran rarely. With
respect to Afghanistan, in 1998, 19 cases (12 fatal) were reported in
Takar Province -- serological tests were not confirmatory. While this
article refers to an outbreak this summer with 6 deaths, there is also
mention of an outbreak last year in the east of Iran with a resultant 14
deaths, suggesting that CCHF is now "resident" in the country (enzootic).
ProMED-mail would be interested in further information on these outbreaks.
- Mod.MPP
[In nature, the reservoir is believed, by some to be hares and birds and
the _Hyalomma_ spp of ticks in Russia. The reservoir hosts remain undefined
in Africa, but _Hyalomma_ and _Boophilus_ ticks, insectivores and rodents
may be involved. Domestic animals such as sheep, goats, and cattle may act
as amplifying hosts during epizootics. - Mod.TG
